<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>PkCap and Guilds</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?holydevil">holydevil</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:13 p.m. 21/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> PkCap and Guilds<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I was wondering if the +/- 4 level pk cap applies to guild wars?

<P>If it does does anyone else she how confusion it can get? or how limited it can become since some guilds won't be able to go to war with others. Or if two guilds go to war it will be weird if like only two guys can fight for a whole guild. Then again maybe it protects new guilds from older ones I guess, but then agian don't both sides need to declare war? So I feel that if both guilds decide to declare war that the cap should be removed, sure that lowely level guy wont do much damage but if he is a cleric he can heal, a wizard can cast protective spells, etc. I would hate to be on the sidelines when my guild is fighting just because I might be a low level
<P>thought please....
<BR>HolyDevil
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
